.TH "ec_i2c_construct_message" 9 "ec_i2c_construct_message" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ec_i2c_construct_message \- construct a message to go to the EC
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ec_i2c_construct_message
.BI "(u8 *buf "  ","
.BI "const struct i2c_msg i2c_msgs[] "  ","
.BI "int num "  ","
.BI "u16 bus_num "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "buf" 12
The buffer to fill.  We assume that the buffer is big enough.
.IP "i2c_msgs" 12
The i2c messages to read.
.IP "num" 12
The number of i2c messages.
.IP "bus_num" 12
The remote bus number we want to talk to.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

This function effectively stuffs the standard i2c_msg format of Linux into
a format that the EC understands.

Returns 0 or a negative error number.
